text: Outside off on a length, Uthappa defends it towards cover-point. This has been a bit different from him this season.

shortText: Mohammed Siraj to Uthappa, no run
text: Trying to do something different. Three of nine now for Uthappa. Walked towards the off side and used his wrists to try and play it wide of mid-on. Finds Rawat there, just short of him.

Managed to breach the fortress on the off side. In the sixth stump line on a length, Uthappa frees his arms and cuts it through cover-point. The point, cover-point and covers were quite tight and yet he found the gap.
Pushes it towards mid-off for a quick one, where Faf misfields.
preText:
Akash Deep to bowl the final over of the powerplay. A wide slip, short third and backward point in position. Covers and mid-off complete the circle on the off side.

"It pains me, it physically pains me to see Faf in RCB colors. " Get used to it now, Ram.

text: Length ball around off, flicked aerially to the man in the deep in front of square on the leg side.
Back of a length on the pads, gets an inside edge onto his pads for a single.

shortText: Akash Deep to Uthappa, no run
text: Once again Uthappa trying something different. Gets a length ball outside off, on his pads as he is already outside off. Misses the flick though.
Straight as arrow for a maximum! Will this get Uthappa and CSK going? In the slot outside off, goes straight over the bowler's head for a 76-metre hit.

shortText: Akash Deep to Uthappa, 1 leg bye
text: Short ball, misses the pull. Gets it off the back thigh for a leg bye. 35/1 at the end of the powerplay.
On a length around off, Uthappa goes for the punch but gets an inside edge onto his back pad.
preText: Big show on! Glenn Maxwell. To Uthappa first up. 100th IPL match for Maxi. Starts from around the stumps.

text: Flatter around off, punched off the back foot through midwicket for one.
A bit short outside off, Moeen presents a straight bat off the back foot.
preText: Footmarks already outside the left-hander's off stump. Moeen has been dismissed twice by Maxwell in the 15 balls he has faced from him in T20 cricket

wkt_text: MM Ali run out 3 (16m 8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 37.50
text: Sensational fielding display. Suyash Prabhudessai making an impression early in the game. Flatter and quicker outside off, cut towards backward point. Seemed to be passing the fielder but for a diving stop. Moeen was down in search of a run and stood no chance of getting back after an accurate throw to the wicketkeeper.
Full on off, driven back.
preText: Shivam Dube in at four in the seventh over.

text: Outside off this time, played through cover to get going.
Timed nicely. Angling away on a length, punched through point for one.
preText: Sachinfan: "that runout was poetry in motion"

text: Placed well. On a length well outside off, Uthappa just had to guide it past short third man. Sways back and does so. His second four.
Back of a length on off, punched down to long-on for one.
Second four in the over. Erring in line, Akash Deep, pays the price. Short but well down leg, gets enough bat to get it fine to the leg side fence.

shortText: Akash Deep to Dube, no run
text: Middles the push straight to covers. Was angling away on a length.

shortText: Akash Deep to Dube, no run
text: Shortish again, makes room but finds backward point with the push. Ten runs off the over, the most expensive so far.
Quicker on the leg, misses the flick. Maxwell appeals but he is the only one.
preText: Arjun Yadav : "Not understanding this slow paced batting from CSK. Bowling has been there problem so far. They need to make atleast 20 runs more than the par score and for that purpose they need to capitalise powerplay. " RCB have not allowed them to get off the blocks quickly.

text: Quicker around leg, pushed through wide mid-on for one.
Slower through the air around off, guided to short third.
Dube goes high and long. Leading run-getter so far for CSK and shows in the confidence. Tossed up around middle, in his arc. Swings his arm for a 94-metre six over long-on.
Slower through the air around middle and leg, defended.
Half-tracker outside off, punched to the sweeper for one.
postText: Nine overs done and it's time for the first time-out of the match. I suspect a lot of talking will be done in the CSK camp than the RCB one. "A bit of hold on the surface for the spinners and we could get the job done," says Maxwell about the surface talking to the broadcaster via the spider-cam.

shortText: Shahbaz Ahmed to Dube, no run
text: Almost sneaks through. Tossed up outside off, Dube looks to flick it away, gets it off the inside edge to short fine leg.
preText: The left-arm spin of Shahbaz Ahmed now.

text: Quicker on middle, worked through square leg for one.
A touch short outside off, slapped to deep point for one.
Floated full outside off, worked away with the turn through midwicket for a single.
Short again and wide, a bit of turn. Uthappa goes back and has to reach out as he gets it through covers for one.
Saw Dube charging down and shortened his length a touch. Worked away through square leg for one. Good start for Shahbaz.
postText: Both Faf and DK are seen having a word with Shahbaz after the over.

shortText: de Silva to Dube, no run
text: Tossed up wrong one, Dube goes for the big one immediately but connects with only thin air.
preText: Wanindu Hasaranga is into the attack. Hasn't had the best of times against lefties. Maruti Suzuki ASKcricinfo stat: Here's a Wanindu Hasaranga's bowling average against right- and left-handers in IPL 2022.

text: Connects and connects well. Tossed up ball around middle again, full enough for Dube to connect. Sends it into the orbit over long-on for half a dozen.
Flatter and quicker outside off, slapped past the diving cover fielder for one.
Tossed up around off, gets it off the inner half through backward square leg for one.
Dube manages to fined the gap. Short in length, Dube goes back deep in the crease and pulls it through midwicket. Splits the gap in the deep to earn for more.
preText: Long-on, deep midwicket and deep square leg on the leg side.

text: Fuller on the pads, driven to long-on for a single to retain strike. Productive over that, 13 coming off it.
preText: Gets deep midwicket finer.

text: Shortish around off, cramps Dube for room. Does well to nudge it through square leg for one.
Shortish again, Uthappa goes back to cut it through point for a couple. A bit less turn meant that he could make good contact.
Flatter and shorter outside off, punched straight to sweeper for one.
preText: Chants of Kohli, Kohli at the DY Patil.

text: Pure timing but Prabhudessai at it again. This time he runs to his right from deep point and saves a couple. It was a full ball outside off, Dube timed it well to get past backward point.
Dube is in the mood. Clears the longest part of the ground with ease. Floated full around middle, goes with the turn and clears deep midwicket.
Flatter outside off, pushed to covers for a single to bring up the 50-run partnership off just 32 balls.
preText: Shahbaz comes around the wicket.
postText: Srividya : "Seeing lots of Yuvi in Shivam. Especially the way he loads for the hoicks!!! "

text: Floated around off, chips it to long-on for one.
preText: Maxwell is back on.

text: Uthappa goes big and gets half a dozen! Half-tracker around middle and leg, quick to pounce on hit and pull it over deep midwicket.
Hello everyone, I am here too, says Uthappa with back-to-back sixes. Tossed up full ball around middle, slog swept over deep midwicket.
Quicker outside off, steered straight to short third.
Quicker on off, punched to wide mid-off.
Three sixes in the over and Uthappa has changed gears seamlessly. Gets another full ball in his zone that he deposits 15 rows back over deep midwicket. 19 off the over.
preText: Two sixes followed by two dots. What's in store now?
postText:
45 runs off the last three overs. CSK opt for the time-out now. Breathing space for RCB as well.

Qaaid: "I thought this was supposed to be a good pitch for spinners...they're all getting hammered"

shortText: de Silva to Dube, no run
text: Bamboozled! Googly on a length around middle, Dube is unsure of which way it will go. Misses it completely and the bounce takes it over the stumps.
preText:
58 runs off the last five overs. Our forecaster predicts CSK to get to 172 at this point. Whom do RCB turn to? Remember, there's no Harshal Patel tonight. Hasaranga it is again. Change of ends.

Vamshhi: "CSK is making good use of left right combination here. RCB surely misses Harshal in these middle overs"

text: Glenn Maxwell you superman! Athletic effort from the Big Show. But he signals four at the end of it. Covers a lot of ground to his left from long-on, pushes the ball back in play as he dives over the ropes. But his last contact was the boundary cushions and is four as a result. Dube had hit the slog high in the air in the vacant deep midwicket region.
Half a chance gone down! Floated around leg, slog-swept it towards deep square leg. The fielder hares to his right, gets low with the dive but fails to catch it.
All going CSK's way now. Dube misses the smash and the googly misses the bat as well as the wicketkeeper for four byes.
Fuller on the pads, pushed towards midwicket for one.
Fired side arm down the leg side, Dube looks to paddle it but doesn't.
Quicker legspinner around off, punched to long-on for one. 12 runs off this over. Fourth successive over in excess of 12 for CSK.

shortText: Akash Deep to Uthappa, no run
text: An appeal for caught behind but it was the bat hitting the ground. Misses the hit through the off side of a ball that was outside.
preText:
Akash Deep is back.

Quite humid out there in Navi Mumbai. Uthappa gets a towel to wipe his face soaked in sweat.

prabin: "unlike cricinfo's forecaster, I predict a score to be 190. rest wait to watch." Machine vs human, ehh?

text: Half-century for Uthappa, 27th in the IPL, second this season. Excellently paced knock this. Full on middle and leg, flicked it through midwicket for four.
Short ball angling in, Uthappa gets inside the line and just helps it over fine leg. He's turning it on.

shortText: Akash Deep to Uthappa, no run
text: Good comeback. A yorker well wide of the batter, reaches out and just toe ends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length on off, gets it high on the bat towards mid-off as he looks to pull it.
preText: Faf has a few words with Akash.

text: Fifty for Dube, now! Second this season to go with a 49. Very full outside off, just slices it over a leaping backward point and gets four. How well has the young Mumbai lad batted today! Superb.
preText: More chat between the bowler and the captain. Long-on in place, mid-off in the circle.

text: Great effort in the deep by Prabhudessai! Uthappa walks down early against Hazlewood, who shortens his length a touch. Goes with the heave that lands short of the man running in from midwicket. Gets one.
preText:
No Harshal, make do with Hazlewood. RCB bring back their spearhead.

Chan: "Is there dew?" Not much right now. They had sprayed the chemical before the start of the innings.

text: Length ball on middle, mistimes his heave through midwicket and gets just one.
preText: Change of bats for Dube now.
postText: Chan: "Is there dew?"

text: Walloped to bring up the 100-run partnership! Uthappa has changed gears in some style. Hard lengths won't work, Swann had said at the pitch report. Banged short, pulled handsomely over deep midwicket for another maximum.
Similar back of a length ball, Uthappa goes for the pull but misses.
Very full outside off, driven to sweeper for one.
Very full on middle, squeezed through midwicket. It is the longer side of the ground and the batters run back for two.
preText: Talk about stepping it up. The first fifty runs of the partnership took 32 balls coming. The next fifty? Only 22.

text: Very full down leg, misses the flick.

shortText: Mohammed Siraj to Uthappa, no run
text: Howzzat? Off the pads. Misses the pull off the length ball but the ball travels straight to short fine.
preText:
Siraj to bowl out. Three overs for 19 so far.

Deepak: "Ex-RCBians performing well against RCB - Nothing new to see here!"

text: Aims London, goes America! Looks to flick the length ball over the on side, but the leading edge takes it over third man for a maximum.
This time it is more authoritative and hit with disdain. Length ball in the slot again, Uthappa dances down and hits it straight as an arrow.
preText: Shiva : "From CSK perspective, wish the RCB faceoff happened bit early in the tournament "

text: Three boundaries? Siraj thinks he has his man lbw. RCB go for the review. But replays confirm that Uthappa got bat to it as he walked across to scoop it past short fine leg.

shortText: Mohammed Siraj to Uthappa, no run

text: Does well. Low full toss outside off, hit straight to long-off for one.

shortText: Mohammed Siraj to Uthappa, 1 no ball
text: Length ball on the pads, hit straight to the fielder at deep square leg. But Siraj has overstepped.
Clean as a whistle (podu)! Very full on middle and leg, hit wayyy over long-on for half a dozen.
preText: Akash Deep now. From around the stumps 34 off his three overs so far. Has a task of breaking the highest partnership in this season so far.

text: Gets the pull over the wicketkeeper's head and takes two. Makes it despite the direct hit at the batter's end.
That slipped off Akash Deep's hand. High full toss outside wide outside off. Dube connects and slams it over point for six more.
Short in length, pulled off the glove to short fine leg for a single.
This is fired down leg, misses the flick. Wide given.
It's a full toss outside off, hit through midwicket for one. 58/0 off four overs for Akash Deep tonight.
preText: Now Siraj has something to say to Akash. How does he finish the over?

text: Another one well outside off, Uthappa leaves it alone.
Another one full and outside the tramline. Wide given again.

That is well wide. Was it on the pitch? Uthappa tells the umpire it wasn't and should be a no ball. But replays show it just landed on the strip. Uthappa had moved across and that forced Akash to fire it wider.
preText: Maxwell helping Akash Deep set the field now. Third man and deep point in place.

text: Glorious maximum. Sees the flighted googly, slinked down and hit it straight towards the sight-screen. IPL best score for Uthappa.
preText:
Hasaranga now for his third. 0/22 so far. Uthappa marks his guard again.

Anish: "Last wicket to fall was like yesterday. "

shortText: de Silva to Uthappa, 1 leg bye
text: Goes for the switch hit now, doesn't connect. Gets it off the thigh for a leg-bye.
Hasaranga's record against southpaws only gets worse. Dube ensures that. Wrong'un on a length, Dube goes back and lifts it over long-on for a 92-metre six.
Fired in on a length, powered down the ground for a single.
preText: Just 14 balls for the fourth fifty for CSK.

wkt_text: RV Uthappa c Kohli b de Silva 88 (98m 50b 4x4 9x6) SR: 176.00
text: Finally a wicket for RCB and Hasaranga! Breaks the 165-run stand. The non-celebration from the Royall Challengers says it all. Was a googly on the shorter side, Uthappa picks Kohli at deep midwicket to perfection to walk back with 88 against his name.

wkt_text: RA Jadeja c Anuj Rawat b de Silva 0 (2m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: Just a one-ball stay for the skipper. Hasaranga has two-in-two but that's it from him tonight. Tossed up googly around middle, Jadeja goes for the slog. Gets it high in the air. Rawat at deep midwicket settles underneath it and takes it safely. Something to cheer for RCB.
preText: Captain Ravindra Jadeja.

text: Effortless, brilliant and maximum. Hazlewood goes for the yorker but misses it not by much. Dube gets under it and hits the biggest six - 102 metres - over long-on. Moves to 86.
preText: MS Dhoni walks out to a loud reception. Final over and Dhoni are stuff of tales. Dube is on strike though. To face Hazlewood.

text: Misses one. Full toss but misses the flick. Goes off the strap of the pad to the keeper.
preText: Can Dube get a ton.

text: Short in length, misses the pull completely.
preText: Sarat : "Uthapppa and Dube proved that both machine and human are wrong..." The forecaster has moved to 215 now.

text: Number one of that! Short in length and on the body. Dube connects the pull and it sails over deep square leg. On 92 now.
preText: Dube needs to hit all to the fence in order to get to his century. Incoming?

shortText: Ali to du Plessis, no run
text: tossed up, Faf turns it gently into the leg side and looks for a single but Moeen is quick to get across
preText: Welcome back, peeps. Interesting from CSK. They'll open with Moeen. Faf on strike. Let's go.

text: this time he's off the mark, tapped into the gap at midwicket

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: drifting into middle and leg from around the wicket, turned to short fine
preText: A slip in place for Rawat

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: shortish and spinning away from outside off, Rawat thinks of a slap but lets it go in the end

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: how did that miss the stumps? Rawat attempts an ambitious reverse sweep to a fyull delivery drifting in, just misses leg stump.

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: tossed up on the stumps, Rawat lunges forward and pats it gently

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to du Plessis, no run
text: slants a length ball across, Faf drives on the up to cover point
preText: Mukesh Choudhary from the other end

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to du Plessis, 3 runs
text: heaved into the leg side. Comes off a thickish inside edge and they will take three. Faf stepped out to have a big swing but didn't control it as well as he would've liked.
preText: Time for our Maruti Suzuki ASKcricinfo stat: Most runs in the last ten overs of an IPL match.

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to Anuj Rawat, 1 run
text: full and swinging away, Rawat plays with an angled bat as the thick edge runs down to third man

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to du Plessis, 3 runs
text: flicked and into the gap at midwicket. This is a half-volley angling into the pads, two more as Jadeja comes up with a sliding stop

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to Anuj Rawat, 3 runs
text: steps out but is cramped for room as Choudhary bangs one in, Rawat goes through with a short-arm jab and gets it into the gap at midwicket. They hare back for the third

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to du Plessis, no run
text: skiddy length ball back into middle, defended gently.
preText: Siddhesh: "Mukesh lucky he is at CSK who traditionally give a long rope to whomever they try. Time for him to repay the faith and make good on the initial promise he showed in the first game." -- If you get a game as a youngster, it's the place to be in. If you don't, it could be a long, long season.

text: slashes at this, well stopped at backward point
preText: Theekshana comes into the attack

text: drifting into middle and leg, worked through midwicket as they jog the single
gorgrous cover drive but down to wide long-off

shortText: Theekshana to du Plessis, no run
text: shortish and angling in, Faf backs away and pulls but mistimes it to square leg

wkt_text: F du Plessis c Jordan b Theekshana 8 (13m 9b 0x4 0x6) SR: 88.88
text: swung away but can't clear long-on. Faf had a grimace as he made contact. First wicket in the IPL for Theekshana and it's a massive one. Faf can't make a big one against his former team.
can't pierce the gap at square leg, pulled straight to Moeen.

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: nice drift into middle and off from around the wicket, defended
terrific from Rawat! Picks the length early, uses the depth of the crease to go back and whip it between midwicket and mid-on

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: reverse-swept straight to short third
rocks back to pull but hits it straight to Jadeja at wide mid-on, they scamper a quick single that brings Kohli on strike
gets forward fully as he pushes it into the off side for a quick single

shortText: Ali to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: in-drifter around off-stump from wide of the crease, carefully kept out

wkt_text: V Kohli c Dube b Mukesh Choudhary 1 (7m 3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33
text: he has picked out deep square! Dube takes a good catch running in grom the ropes. Mukesh bowls length, gets it to nip back into middle, Kohli whips it uppishly - the timing is good - but it's as if he forgot there was a man in the deep precisely for that.
runs it down to third man to get off the mark
preText: Maxwell is in earlier than he would've expected

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to Anuj Rawat, no run
text: this is a beauty! Gets the ball to jag away off a length to square Rawat

shortText: Mukesh Choudhary to Anuj Rawat, 1 run
text: steps out to smash that down the ground but toe-ends this flat-batted hit, lands between mid-on and mid-off
hammered! Picks the length early and pulls him imperiously in front of square
uppish and on the bounce to Jadeja at mid-off, Maxwell had given up. A direct hit at the bowler's end would've had him
flatter on middle and leg, tucked to the man coming in from deep square. DJ Bravo fumbles to allow a second.
attempts an audacious reverse hit over point but gave away his intentions way too early, smashed a thick edge onto his pad
he's clobbered that over long-off! Not entirely in his half but he went after that one and biffed it magnificently
six more! This one's over deep midwicket. Theekshana drops short, Maxwell latches onto it in a jiffy. He's in a murdeous mood
just eludes Jadeja, who runs back from mid-off to make a valiant effort. The ball was always skewing away from him, two more. Maxwell wasn't in control

wkt_text: Anuj Rawat lbw b Theekshana 12 (28m 16b 1x4 0x6) SR: 75.00
text: got him with a super delivery! Theekshana takes off on a celebratory run that would make Imran Tahir proud. Rawat has reviewed. This one cuts back in sharply to beat Rawat, who tries to whip that across the line. He's hit on the back pad and the ball didn't have a long way to travel. he got into a terrible tangle there and ball tracking comes back to show three reds.
slapped disdainfully! Drops short, Maxwell rocks back ns flays that through cover. Mukesh Choudhary with a dive from deep point but couldn't stop it despite a slide
punched past the bowler to long-on
ah, so very delightful. Width outside off, he rocks back and cuts late to beat backward point
pushed into the gap at point for an easy single

wkt_text: GJ Maxwell  b Jadeja 26 (15m 11b 2x4 2x6) SR: 236.36
text: got him! Maxwell is beaten by the fizz on this arm ball. Swung through a tad early and missed. The length wasn't quite there to pull. This one rushed onto him as well. RCB in tatters.
jabbed back down the pitch
preText: IPL debutant Suyash Prabhudesai comes in

text: welcome boundary, but CSK won't mind. Shahbaz sweeps him uppishly but into the gap at square leg.
uses the depth of the crease to nicely work it through square leg
steps out and swings this one bounce to long-on
worked past a vacant midwicket region

oh dear, the fielder at deep midwicket has put it down. Mukesh Choudhary didn't pick that, by the time he moved to his right and put in a dive, the ball had swirled away. Suyash with his first boundary through a slog sweep
worked into the leg side for a single
bludgeoned! Pure power. Cleared his front leg and used the width to belt that through extra cover.
worked past square leg as he jogs the single
shortish on middle and leg, nurdled into the gap at midwicket, two more

shortText: Jadeja to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run
text: breaks back in off a length to hit him on the body as he tries to work it to the leg side

shortText: Jadeja to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run
text: sharp turn once again, kept out somehow
swept into the gap at deep backward square leg. Got down on one knee and swept him up and over with the angle
width and Suyash has hammered that through cover! Flat-batted it with a touch of arrogance
gentle bunt to point for a quick single
slower and fuller on off, eased wide of point for a quick single
cheeky and very effective! AB would've be proud of that. Goes down on one knee, keeps his eyes on the ball all along as he scoops it over Dhoni for four.
preText: Sabarish: "Why has CSK picked Jordan ahead of Pretorius?" -- A question many people are asking.
postText: Nikhil Vasudev: "Lucky u shashank u didn't have to type the csk innings other wise it will be more typing and typing." -- You bet

text: slips this length ball into middle and leg, turned to deep square
width on offer, flayed into the gap at deep point
whips this to deep midwicket
fired full on leg stump, tucked to square leg, excellent running to hare back for the second
flatter one on the stumps, tucked to Rayudu at square leg
reverse swept over short third! May have given his intentions of the reverse but kept his eyes on the ball all through as he exected it superbly
bye bye ball! Walloped over deep square leg. Down on one knee, across and outside the line as he uses the angle coming in to give it a tonk with the slog sweep. What a hit
pushed through quicker on off, slapped straight to cover

shortText: Bravo to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run
text: beaten as he has a big swipe at that
starts off with a slower ball that he bowls way outside the tram line
preText: DJ Bravo

text: low full toss and he has absolutely drilled this into the gap between wide long-off and deep extra cover.
slips this too far wide outide off, Shahbaz who took a step across to meet the ball let it pass
dabs it to short third for a quick single

oh my word! Mukesh Choudhary has absolutely put down a dolly. This was right down his basket at deep midwicket. Suyash looked to pull but was cramped for room. He was also hitting towards the bigger boundary. Was in no control of the stroke. What a mess
chopped wide of point
drilled to long-on
breaks away from a length outside off, defended back

wkt_text: SS Prabhudessai  b Theekshana 34 (29m 18b 5x4 1x6) SR: 188.88
text: got him! Suyash steps out to hoick him over midwicket but ends up being defeated by the drift and sharp turn away. He swung through a tad early as well, so even if the ball didn't hit the stumps, he would've been stumped. Good knock, terrific intent and we've seen glimpses of something special
preText: Sanyam Kamat: "Very excited to see a fellow local boy from Goa, Suyash Prabhudessai performing in this IPL match. Its a rarity for Goans to play in IPL, only few of the likes of Swapnil Asnodkar and Shadab Jakati have played in IPL before."

text: swept into the gap at fine leg. Down on one knee as he swept him with the angle. DK is up and running immediately.
worked into the gap at midwicket

shortText: Theekshana to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run
text: mix-up but safe. Shahbaz pushed it to cover, wanted a run only to be sent back
swept to deep square leg
just out of Theekshana's grasp at short third. Shahbaz went after that but ended up slicing it behind square ont he off side. Valiant effort
slower ball but way outside the line, wide called
drilled into the gap at sweeper point
slower length ball outside off, punched to deep cover
dipping yorker, driven down to wide long-off as they scamper a second
slants a slower length ball across, Karthik bunts it gently to point. Now, now. He has overstepped. Freehit coming up. The no ball is for having more than two fielders behind square on the leg side.
punched into the gap at deep cover, two more
punched to long-off
length on middle, tucked to square leg
preText: Theekshana into his final over

text: he hasn't timed this and <s> Mukesh takes a catch at point. </s> Oh my word. he has put that down. Everyone around him can't believe it. Karthikl looked to go over long-off but got nowhere to the pitch and ended up slicing it high in the air. Mukesh took a couple of steps back from point, kept his eyes on the swirler but was never steady underneath it. Tough, tough evening for the young man.
preText: Madhusudan H J: "Win or Lose, impressed by RCBs intent here. RCB always folded under 120 when trying a high chase."

wkt_text: Shahbaz Ahmed  b Theekshana 41 (47m 27b 4x4 0x6) SR: 151.85
text: got him this time! Don't need anyone's assistance to pick wickets if you can bowl magicballs like that. It's the carromball that fizzes back in off a length to hurrty Shahbaz into a defensive stroke. Sneaked through the gap to smash into the stumps
pushed wide of point to get off the mark
clears deep backward sqaure leg! Some level of premeditation as Karthik walks across a long way and wallops him with the spin
looks to work it to the leg side but can only hit it back to the bowler

preText:
7.27pm The Sunrisers huddle is done, the umpires are in the middle. Bhuvi has taken his hat off. Gill and Wade for Titans. This venue has seen the most sixes so far in the comp.

Bhaskara Navulu: "Why is the list of playing 11 not published so far. Yeah I know the teams are unchanged. But it's a bit of non-cricinfo to not publish the playing 11 after the toss" -- Hi Bhaskara! We have a shiny new "tab" in the scorecard called "Playing XI" - do check that out!

Krishnan: "Gill the other day reminded one of Sir IVAR. Such regal strokeplay. Including the gum chewing swagger. Hope for a repeat."

Henri: "Replace toss with auction. Teams would auction with runs given to opponent as currency. "Team X chose to field and give 3 extra runs to Team Y.""

Mustafa Moudi : "@Henri: Do you want the losing captain to have no relief at all ?? At least they can blame the toss now but if auction happens, every one will blame the losing captain for being Over/Under Confident during the toss/auction!!"

Krish D: "Why isnt Yash Dayal or Sai Kishore playing? Both have been outstanding in domestic cricket. Defo deserve a chance" -- I'm sure the Titans will give them a shot at the right time. They've invested time into Abhinav Manohar and now Sai Sudharshan, so let's hope this duo gets a longish rope first.

Siddhartha Kuma: "I don't know about you but I am tuned in to see who wins the fastest delivery money here.. I am putting my chips on ferguson" -- Probably the best battle of the competition with Umran on the other side.

Sumit Gnawali: "During auction teams didn't bid for legspinner that much but imp of leg spinner has increased in last few games or Am i wrong ?" -- Indian legspinners/wristspinners are in very high demand. But spin bowlers appear quite late in the auction, batters and allrounders appear before them, so that's why they probably get fewer bidding wars.

Here's a revealing Maruti Suzuki ASKcricinfo stat for you: Which team has the worst run rate in powerplay overs at IPL 2022?

7pm toss The coin goes up. Sunrisers Hyderabad opt to bowl.

Kane Williamson: "Potential dew factor can make a difference. But want to put skills with ball up front. (CSK win) Largely it was about growth. We improved in the second game and a win in the third. Hope to do that today too. We need to be adaptable with the grounds. Same XI."

Hardik Pandya: "We would've bowled as well. Playing here for the first time so doesn't matter, batting first is okay. (Success as captain) Always good to win but for us results are important but processes are more important. We have got the results since we have been following the plans. This game is more important for us, we need to show we are putting in the hard work. (Tewatia as a finisher) The way he is batting, the confidence he says, it shows courage and character. Being confident is helping him. Same XI."

Shashank: "Kane 4/4 in tosses. Please pass on some luck to my fantasy team !!"

6.58pm Just two minutes till the toss. The team winning the toss has chased in all 20 games so far!

In other news, Royal Challengers Bangalore will be without Harshal Patel tomorrow. Harshal lost a family member yesterday. When he returns, he will have to serve a three-day quarantine before playing. Our prayers are with him in these difficult times. Full story here.

Those of you in the US can watch the action live on ESPN+ in English or in Hindi.

Pitch and ground: This is not the centre pitch, so one square boundary is shorter than the other (64m, compared to 74m). Good batting pitch but it will be "a bit slow, and it will turn," according to Daren Ganga.

6.50pm Just ten minutes for the toss. Will Umran Malik make the cut for the Sunrisers XI? Here's how Wasim Jaffer wants SRH to use the young quick. Also a good time to check out our Fantasy cricket tips.

Krishna: "Unpopular opinion but Kane should open for SRH. He takes time to settle more often that not and opening gives him the opportunity to do that. At the same time he's better equipped and experienced to tackle the new ball danger giving space for batters coming in later to play freely. Even while chasing it doesn't matter if he plays slowly as long as he stays till the point where his dismissal doesn't cause a collapse nor hurts the Chase."

Samrat Ahuja: "Would/Should GT persist with Wade? or go with Gurbaz . being from subcontinent, he would be better prepared to play on these pitches!" -- It is a punt worth taking for sure! But in a winning combination, it is hard to see Wade miss out.

6.41pm For the Titans, it has been quite a ride so far. At the start of the season, they were considered "weaker" given that their didn't appear to be any synergy in their squad and XI. But after three games, all those doubts have been put to rest, with Shami-Ferguson-Rashid being the key bowling enforcers, and Gill-Hardik-Tewatia-Miller doing enough between them to lead the batting attack. They have the pace and the spin to trouble Sunrisers today too - they have been susceptible against extra pace. And despite Gujarat's excellent run, there is still some room for improvement. Here's Sanjay Manrejkar and Wasim Jaffer talking about today's contest.

KB: "Should we put an end to the debate of where Williamson should play? " -- I thought he would play at No. 4 and push Tripathi/Markram up to open in the last game, but since that didn't happen, I don't see it happening after a win.

6.33pm Hello! Peter Della Penna and Sreshth Shah here at your service to bring you all the action from match 21 of IPL 2022. Today we're coming to you from Navi Mumbai's DY Patil Stadium where Sunrisers Hyderabad will take on Gujarat Titans.

The Titans are unbeaten, looking for a fourth win in a row, and their trump card tonight could be the man who played such a big role in the rise of Sunrisers Hyderabad - Rashid Khan. He could very well get his 100th IPL wicket against his former side. Here's our match preview penned by Sruthi Ravindranath.

preText: Scores level now.
postText:
11.18 pm So Pooran replaces the injured Tripathi in the 14th over and stays to the end to clinch victory. Captain Williamson gets a half-century in victory too.

Titans captain Hardik Pandya: "Batting wise I think we were 7-10 runs short and would've made a difference in the end. Bowling wise, we had a good start but had two bad overs. I think they bowled well [in the last 5 overs]. The bounce was varying about and their bowlers with different heights. Credit to them with the way they bowled. Our motto has been the same which is to learn from the mistakes we make no matter the result. In a couple of days we have our next game. Relax and enjoy the game."

Nicholas Pooran from Sunrisers: "We as a batting group wanted to learn from our mistakes in the past and make partnerships. It was challenging because it was two-paced. The slower balls were sticking in the wicket a bit. We just needed a partnership, not do anything stupid and be there at the end. I try to improve every single day that I train and play. We have some amazing coaches that sit with us and have some amazing conversations. Brian is helping us tremendously, not just me but all the young batters. The first over [in the field] went wrong for us, but having saying that with the dropped catches and extras, 160 on that wicket was fabulous for the bowlers."

Kane Williamson is named Player of the Match: "It was I thought all in all a good game of cricket. I thought we were good with the ball and so were they. It was hard to get a rhythm and so we just tried to build partnerships but good to see signs of improvement. The guys are nice and clear on their roles. Naturally there are always a number of challenges playing the best in the world and you're always under pressure but they adjusted nicely. It was quite tough to hit through the line. It was a fair game of cricket and if you could pick up wickets you could squeeze them a little bit. I think [Tripathi] might just be cramp. Hopefully it is minor and he can recover quickly. I'm not quite sure about Washington Sundar but hopefully he recovers quickly. We're seeing a variety of surfaces throughout the comp so I'm just trying to adjust."

That's it for our live commentary coverage today. Come back tomorrow for more IPL action. Take care!

preText:
7.30pm Chameera to Buttler.

Nick: "@Anubhav : I guess Parag stays there because they need an allrounder. In the first match, Coulter-Nile was injured so they needed a 6th bowler !"

Anubhav: "Both Parag and Jaiswal have had bad runs, Parag for much longer, but it is Jaiswal who is dropped? Why does Rajasthan have such fascination with a player who has performed average for a long time now? (note: if parag performs I will gladly eat my words)"

7.10pm Mahesh: "Finally Rassie gets a game. He walks into my fantasy dream 11 right away" -- Good choice! He wasn't in our "recommended XI" for this match, which you should check out.

Ramji : "Padikkal will open. Samson at 3 and Rvdd at 4. " -- Equally nice idea. Probably better than Buttler and Samson at 1 and 2. Agree.

ESPN+ plug: Those of you in the USA can watch this game live on ESPN+.

KD: "The balance of this LSG team is unreal. Hope KL takes the aggressive route now too"

So to summarise, Super Giants have strengthened their bowling further by adding eight overs of Chameera and Stoinis in place of AJ Tye and Evin Lewis. Bowling pace goes up for sure, now to see where exactly Stoinis bats. As for the Royals, Kuldeep Sen is a right-arm quick from Madhya Pradesh. The tall 25-year old has T20 bowling economy of 8.20 and can bowl a mean yorker according to a quick check of his bowling on YouTube. Whether van der Dussen opens (unlikely) or Samson goes up to opener in Jaiswal's absence is to be seen.

Sumith: "Proactive changes by the Royals. It's not pressing the panic button but realising the importance for winning momentum. "

7pm Toss Lucknow opt to bowl. "No reason other than dew and knowing what to chase," KL Rahul said. "Every game is fresh. I am looking to come out and do the job. I will know a target so will try to pace to the best of my availability. Leadership has been good. We have a good team, that makes job of a captain easy. 9 or 10 of our starters play at the top level, so that makes it easy. They know their roles. Two changes as Lewis, Tye miss out. Stoinis and Chameera come in.

"We'll see how this total behaves before we set a target accordingly," Sanju Samson said. "Nothing to do with the toss so we have a team that can do well with any toss decision. Kuldip Sen instead of Navdeep Saini, Rassie van der Dussen replaces Yashasvi Jaiswal.

Akshaye: "That's 4 out of 4 tosses lost for Sanju"

6.55pm Last week we had R Ashwin with us, this week it is James Neesham who joins ESPNcricinfo on #PoliteEnquiries. Here's what twitter's Mr. funny had to say.

Ramji V: "Will stoinis walk in directly into XI? Who is vulnerable in that case?Lewis Or Tye? " -- Stoinis is available, but I am not totally convinced that he walks into the XI. Lewis has useful at the top, Holder is doing his job well, and Tye ensures the bowling is stocked up in an XI that bats deep anyway with Gowtham also in the team. Let's see.

Maruti Suzuki ASKcricinfo stat: Compare the strike rates of Rahul and Buttler at the Wankhede...

6.40pm Hello and welcome to the evening clash of Super Sunday. We are twenty minutes away from the toss of this big encounter with Rajasthan Royals taking on Lucknow Super Giants. For both these sides, today's encounter could be the day that they solidify their positions in the top of the points table. The key battle will be between the two batting orders, both with powerful players and in form. More in our match preview.

Because he didn't review right away. That would've surprised Padikkal too

up and over! Stands tall and lofts it over Chameera's head. Full, in the slot on off stump, and Padikkal pounced on it in a flash.

preText: Ashish: "Thanks Manish for saying it up (unless Bishnoi's throw was actually wayward). I will never know as I was not watching it live." -- Buttler was in very quickly, the run out was never quite on, and it was too quick a throw from Bishnoi for the one backing up (Gowtham) to get in position. That said, Gowtham could've pre-empted Bishnoi's throw and moved to his left a bit quicker, but tough to do that.

text: good length, on middle and leg. Clipped off his hips to deep backward square leg for a single
full on middle and leg stump. Buttler goes for the fine flick, and its got some pad en route to short fine leg for a single. Umpire confirms it was pad first, with the legbye signal given
good length ball on middle and off. Shuffles onto the off side and fends it off the back foot
back of a length, just outside leg stump. Ducks under it and takes the extra run. This was 144kph
a good comeback over from Chameera after that first-ball four. Length ball angling across and Padikkal guides it to third man for a walking single
postText: Max: "RR is an extremely dangerous and balanced team this year EXCEPT for the all rounders. They really don't have much strength at that position. Which means the specialists can't really have an off day. "

text: full on middle, and flicked with strong wrists to deep midwicket. Padikkal played it before bothering in which direction the ball would turn
preText: Actor Suniel Shetty is in attendance, wearing the Super Giants blue. Here's Ravi Bishnoi now.

text: tossed up on off stump. Pushed to wide long off for a walking single
good length ball on off and middle. Googly turns across his body, and down the leg side
preText: Sarthak: "That throw from Bishnoi was in similar circumstances to the throw he threw to run Gaikwad out.. That day it hit and got the batter out, today it didnt.. worth a shot"

text: length ball, on off, and turning further away. Padikkal hammers this short and wide ball through the off side, and the cut has gone to the boundary
preText: Bishnoi has a slip for both batters. Operating over the stumps for now.

text: another googly. Fuller on off, but turning across. Padikkal capitalises on the width, and punishes Bishnoi with the cut once more

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Padikkal, no run
text: dropped! Classical legspinner's caught and bowled chance, but Padikkal has survived. Full on middle and leg, and Padikkal pressed forward to defend. Met with hard hands, ball went straight back to Bishnoi, but it didn't stick even though he got into a good position, with a straight-on body in prep to gobble the catch
full on off, and driven to long off to keep the strike
full outside off and angling across. Padikkal looks to drive off the front foot, but misses out. Past the bat to the keeper
preText: Run rate of nearly 10. Chameera for a third over.

text: fullish, on middle and leg. Padikkal closes the bat's face and works it to the leg side
attempted yorker, nearly successful. Dug away from middle stump
attempts the yorker again, very nearly lands it. Padikkal mistimes a drive through the off side to get to the other side
full toss around off stump. Surprises Buttler. He bunts it to the leg side - in front of square - for a single
good length ball angling across, and cut to the infielder
back of a length, just outside leg stump. Ducks under it, and given a wide. Not for height, but for the line. Was a close one, but probably a good decision

wkt_text: JC Buttler  b Avesh Khan 13 (30m 11b 1x4 1x6) SR: 118.18
text: what a start to your spell! Buttler's stumps rattled, and Avesh has struck. Full around off stump, angling in to the stumps as Buttler tries to welcome him with a sloggy swipe to long on. Misses the connection, and Avesh hits bulls eye
preText: last over of the powerplay.

text: full just outside off. A gentle drive past cover's left, and they pick up two as Rahul collects the ball from around the boundary line after making a chase
preText: Samson joins Padikkal.
postText: Ram: "Rajasthan Royals are the only team to win 2 games by batting first"

shortText: Avesh Khan to Samson, no run
text: full on leg stump, and clipped in front of square. Samson misses out on the wayward line from Avesh, hitting it to midwicket

shortText: Avesh Khan to Samson, no run
text: good length ball on off stump. Samson expected it to bounce more as he looks to play a punch off the back foot. Mistimed, and it ends up as an inside-edged shot onto his body before rolling away to the off side

shortText: Avesh Khan to Samson, no run
text: fullish just outside off. Samson shuffles across to cover off stump before defending the ball away

shortText: Avesh Khan to Samson, no run
text: just two off his first over. Short ball on leg stump, and left alone by Samson
full, and quite wide outside off. Padikkal slaps a mistimed shot courtesy the width to deep point

tosses it up. Full outside off, and Samson tonks it right over the umpire's head with ease! Bishnoi's legbreaks don't turn as much as the googly, and Samson took full advantage of that. Off the sweet spot
good length on off. Turning into middle. Worked off the back foot to deep midwicket
preText: Dasitha: "Credit should go to the Chameera as well for keeping things tight at one end.. Avesh uses full benefit from that.. This what MI lacks in last few games. No bowler on other end to keep things tight to support Bumrah.. "

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Padikkal, no run
text: good length ball outside off. Angling across as he tries to cut. Quicker delivery and he misses out
full outside leg. Padikkal tries to sweep but misses. The googly didn't turn in much either for a bowled-type dismissal around Padikkal's legs. Wide given
slower through the air. Full on leg, and clipped off the back foot to midwicket

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, no run
text: full on off. Samson expects the googly and therefore plays a heave to the leg side. Straight to midwicket
like a tracer bullet as Padikkal smacks this full ball on off stump down the ground. Too hot for KL Rahul at mid off too, who misfields, and that allows Royals to take the run
lazy elegance as some people like to call it. Length ball on a fourth-stump line. Samson stays on the back foot and plays a cut rather late, and gets it behind backward point for four
good length outside off. Cut again, past point, but man in the deep runs across to intercept

shortText: Avesh Khan to Padikkal, no run
text: fullish ball on off stump. Tapped back to the bowler

shortText: Avesh Khan to Padikkal, no run
text: length ball lands just outside leg and Padikkal tries to play a flick rather fine. Misses the shot, hits the thigh guard, rolls away to the keeper's right

shortText: Avesh Khan to Padikkal, no run
text: full around leg stump. Padikkal misses the flick as the ball angles across and hits his front leg in front of middle stump. Appeal for lbw turned down, that probably either pitched outside leg or took some bat en route to the pad. Time out
108kph slower ball, full outside off stump. Driven with the angled bat to deep point
preText: Holder returns.

text: full on middle and leg. Pushed to midwicket, which is vacant. The outfielder runs in and stops the two

wkt_text: SV Samson lbw b Holder 13 (17m 12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 108.33
text: is he lbw on a full toss? Yes! Slides this full toss into the stumps, and Samson misses the flick from near his knee roll. Hits him, and the umpire has an easy decision to make. Samson does not review

shortText: Holder to van der Dussen, FOUR
text: starts his campaign with a boundary as Holder goes full on leg. Rassie plays it fine, closing the bat's face, and gets it past the keeper's left for four

shortText: Holder to van der Dussen, no run
text: full on off stump. Defended off the front foot

shortText: Holder to van der Dussen, no run
text: good length outside off stump. It's an offcutter. Cut to point. Successful over for Holder

wkt_text: D Padikkal c Holder b Gowtham 29 (51m 29b 4x4 0x6) SR: 100.00
text: around the stumps. Full on off. Padikkal goes for a reverse sweep, but he's top edged it only for first slip to eat him up! Padikkal tried to hit it over conventional short third man, but was through the shot too early. Gowtham starts with a bang
preText: ESPNcricinfo's Forecaster has Royals on course to reach 156. Not enough on this surface against a line-up that bats till No. 8 atleast. Padikkal, who struggles after the powerplay, needs to get a move on. K Gowtham on now, starting the fifth-bowler overs.

text: continues around the stumps to Hetmyer. Full on middle. Bit of offspin on offer. Carefully fended off the back foot
full on off. Clips it square past the umpire with soft hands off the front foot. Calls early for the second run as well
full on middle, and flicked once more. This time to deep midwicket

shortText: Gowtham to van der Dussen, OUT
wkt_text: HE van der Dussen  b Gowtham 4 (9m 4b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00
text: bowled 'im! And Rassie is out after a boundary. Gowtham continues around the stumps. Gets this full ball on middle to go straight through. Rassie misses the cut, the ball goes past the blade, and off stump is broken.
postText: Time for a change in commentary with that wicket and Super Giants on top. Here's Himanshu.

text: good length ball outside off, and dabbed to short third man
preText:
Ashwin the new man in, as Gowtham comes from around the wicket. A leg slip in place.

Thanks Sreshth. A real recovery needed for Royals.

text: zips one at a back of a length just outside off. He has a poke at that, but is beaten by pace
preText: Chameera back. A slip waiting, as he comes from over the wicket.

text: good length ball just outside off, as this keeps just a tad low. Tapped towards over after adjusting for the low bounce
preText: Those of you in the USA can watch this game live on ESPN+.

text: a touch fuller on off at 140kph. Ashwin blocks it to point, as the ball hints to angle away
postText: Manu: "Perfect opportunity for Parag to prove himself tonight..." --- Of course when he comes out to bat

text: drives this fuller ball outside off to point. That made a good sound off the bat, but didn't go far
on the shorter of a good length on off, and clipped expertly to deep midwicket. A reminder of what the Ashwin of old did with the bat. Good chase by long-on running to his right, pulling it back late
phew, this flies past the outside edge now! Ashwin's bat face is half-closed as he tries to clip this fuller ball outside off, as the ball shapes to angle in before moving away late
full ball no off, and driven to deep point
preText: Around the wicket comes Gowtham

text: full again off, and driven to long-off now
preText: Around the stumps to Ashwin too. Leg slip stands.

text: another full delivery on middle and off. Flicked to long-on
good length ball on middle, as he steps across to clip to fine leg
on a good length on off, as he closes the bat face to tuck to midwicket
gets into it with a slog over long-on! Gowtham goes fuller on off, as Hetmyer is down on his knee early to heave that across the line. Makes up for a quiet over until then
low full toss on off, as the ball is tossed up. Pushed to long-off
preText:
Bishnoi back from over the wicket... And Ashwin backs out at the last moment. Perhaps something distracted him near the sightscreen.

Amey: "RR batting is suddenly looking very thin. "

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, no run
text: past the outside edge. Slides this fullish and fast on off, and it turns away, as he has a poke
preText: A word between the batters, as Bishnoi stays over the wicket to the left-hander. A slip there too.

text: shorter in length and outside off. Cut away to deep point
pretty full ball on off, and driven to deep point

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, no run
text: fuller and outside off. Again he has tries to have a dab, but is beaten on the outside edge
shorter in length outside off, and turning away. Cut to point
postText:
Sky: "@Amey From the start of the tournament I've felt that way. Which is why the decision to not play Neesham is bizarre. Adds depth to the batting can bowl in the death. Partially solves the only 2 problems RR have right now."

Time-out

text: full on off, and flatter too. Tapped to cover
preText:
Gowtham will continue.

Seven overs to go. How far can Hetmyer, Ashwin and Parag take this? Our predictor says 145.

text: dropped by Krunal at long-on! That was an easy catch. Hetmyer tries to pull that ball, but it isn't short enough on middle, and neither does he get it off the middle of the bat. Krunal almost seemed unsure how to take it, and ended it somewhere between a reverse cup and his fingers facing the sky
single to deep midwicket, as Ashwin clips this fullish ball which is quicker too on leg
pushed back to the bowler, as the ball is on a good length
fuller on leg, and nudged towards midwicket. The bowler gives the chase
fullish in length and a little wide of off, as Ashwin has a jab but misses

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, no run
text: shorish in length, and wide of off. Finds extra cover with his cut
off the outside edge, but wide of slip. Goes pushing at this fullish ball turning away. Good diving stop to his right at short third man
short of a length on off, and pulled to long-on from deep in the crease
fullish and down the leg side. Left alone, and called wide
leading edge there. Closes the bat face early to that good length ball on off, and somehow manages to get it towards long-off

shortText: Ravi Bishnoi to Ashwin, no run
text: a yorker on middle, and quick and flat. Jammed off the inside edge
gets a bottom edge, as he looks to sweep that full ball outside off. A single behind the wicket
sends that flying over the bowler's head! Boom! Opens the bat face a touch to that full ball on off, and launches into that with his front leg out of the way
preText: Max: "Ravi Ashwin is one of my fav cricketers, but seeing him bat 4 down in a T20 is a bit of a joke tbh. What is RR thinking?"

text: six more, and Ashwin presses the accelerator! Short of a length on leg, and he waits for the ball to come to pull over deep midwicket from deep in the crease
full toss on off, and he lofts that on the bounce to long-off
preText: Over the wicket now

text: short and wide of off, and cut away to the right of deep point
fuller and just outside off. Pushed back to the bowler
preText: Ashish: "Ashwin answers Max in his own style!"

text: this is quicker and on a good length on middle and leg. He clips to short fine leg
back of a length outside off, and punched to point
preText: Avesh from over the wicket
postText: Gagan: "@himanshu: who will win today? Man city or Liverpool?" --- If you ask me, I will hardly be affected by the result. Manchester United can barely manage a win after all.

text: has a swing at that pretty full outside off, but just manages to nudge it to the bowler's right. A single dribbling to long-on
preText: He runs in, but Ashwin backs out... To be reloaded.

text: short of a length just outside off. He taps that to point after getting on top of the bounce
fires a yorker on off, as Ashwin gets an inside edge while trying to slog to the on side. The ball goes to fine leg, as the keeper can't collect the throw cleanly to allow an overthrow
postText: Keyan: "when negative event happens after someone's comment we say Jinx. What is it for Positive event? Max -positive jinx?" --- Reverse jinx?

shortText: Avesh Khan to Ashwin, no run
text: swing and a miss! On a shortish length outside off, and he misses his pull
wide outside off. Too full and too wide. Left alone
lofts that to long-off. Pretty full ball on off at 135kph, and Ashwin mistimes his slog
yorker on leg, as he makes room. Flicked to fine leg
preText:
Holder from over the wicket

Jay: "There is only Parag left who can bat in their line up. From Boult down it is a lottery of sorts. Perhaps Ashwin was sent 1 spot ahead to play a bit sensibly before slogging out"

text: fires that over wide long-on! Right there in his hitting zone on a full length on middle, as he gets his front leg out of the way to launch into that heave
preText: Third man and fine leg up. Holder over the wicket still.

text: has a swing again, but misses this. It was full and pretty wide of off, and angling away further as it was a slower ball
postText: Malli: "This RR team reminds me of SRH few seasons ago, strong bowling lineup, consistent opener and no/thin middle order. It wins when top orders strikes, loses otherwise"

text: hoicked over short fine leg! Has a free swing of the arms to that good length ball on middle, which is angling away. Gets that off the inside edge, but four still
Has that landed in the sea? Drilled over the bowler's head. Takes a step across off, and gets that full length ball outside off. Fires that bang over the bowler's head
change of pace, and short and wide of off. He slaps that to the man at cover-point, and pinches a single
preText: Around the wicket now

text: a near yorker on middle, and crunched to long-on from deep in the crease
preText:
Two overs to go. Anyone for 160?

Bala: "My comments a while back was not published. I had stated that Hetmyer is likely to have fun with the fast bowlers as the quota of Gowtham and Bishnoi are over. It is a reality now." --- You said it...

wkt_text: R Ashwin retired out 28 (40m 23b 0x4 2x6) SR: 121.73
text: full and wide of off, as he drags that to deep point
swatted over deep point! Short and wide of off, and he rides the bounce to slash that far and wide of the man at deep point
preText: Ashwin rushes off the park... He has retired out! Wow!
postText: Arali : "Ashwin has 5 test hundreds - more than the rest of the RR players probably combined, that's not a joke" --- Yes, but I am not sure how much that matters in a T20.

text: slapped over deep midwicket! What has got into him suddenly? Reaches his fifty off 33 balls. Right in the slot on a fullish length on middle, and he swings like freeing himself of pain
has another heave, and gets that on the bounce to deep midwicket. Fuller on middle and leg this time from Avesh
cracks a yorker on middle. Parag jams his bat down late for a single
a slow, dipping full toss on middle and leg. Swung away to fine leg
preText: Sriky: "Always thought retired out is a gully cricket innovation and not a real cricket rule. Wow"

text: all that doesn't matter, as Hetmyer still gets six! A slower ball, and a full toss outside off. He is ready to dispatch that out of the world. Six over deep midwicket
preText: Deep midwicket now pretty straight. Third man out too, with deep point wide. Holder around the wicket.
postText: Ahan: "Retiring someone out is a purely tactical move in t20 and should be seen as such. Hopefully it becomes more mainstream in the near future."

text: makes room, and pulls this short of a length ball wide of off to long-on
preText: Conference between Stoinis, Holder and Rahul now. Holder back over the wicket.

text: another slower ball, another full toss and another six! Parag is down on his knee to send that blazing over fine leg. More pain for Holder
postText: Andrew Evans: "I once retired out in a 3rd XI game as I wasn't scoring. RR must have taken notice of my example." --- Why not? Who knows what happens in the world of so much data and info?

wkt_text: R Parag c Gowtham b Holder 8 (10m 4b 0x4 1x6) SR: 200.00
text: is that a clean catch by Gowtham at fine leg? Yup, looks like. But the umpire will check even as Parag is ready to walk back. A slower-ball bouncer from Holder on off, and he gets extra bounce. Gowtham has to go low, but takes it well in the end

wkt_text: KL Rahul  b Boult 0 (1m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: peach of a ball! Comes around the stumps, bowls full, ball originates outside off but swings in with the angle. Rahul can't get any bat on it with the late swing, and Boult's angle has worked against Rahul! Through the gap between bat and pad as Rahul tried to mow it through the leg side
preText: Welcome back to the chase. de Kock, Rahul and Boult are protagonists for the opening salvo.

wkt_text: K Gowtham lbw b Boult 0 (3m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: two wickets in three balls! The new-ball master is at it. The Gowtham experiment has not worked, Boult too good for him with the new cherry. Boult comes over the stumps. Full on middle, and angling into leg stump. Gowtham can't get bat on ball.
top take by Samson as he flies to his left to grab this one handed. Bowl went full on middle to the No. 3 Gowtham, but went down the leg side courtesy the swing.
full outside off as he searches for the swing. Ends up overpitching. Toe-ends a drive to mid off
preText: Holder at No. 4.
postText: Navin: "Thats pure class from Boult!! But Badoni will be hitting the winning runs today!! "

text: full outside off stump. Pushes at the ball angling away from Holder. No swing
length ball on off, and just going across Holder subtly. He sticks the bat out to try and push at it, but the ball goes past the outside edge. So close!
fullish, wider from Boult, and Holder pounces on it. Good length outside off, and cut behind square, past the packed slip cordon

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to de Kock, no run
text: full ball around the stumps. Swings in and lands on middle. de Kock flicks off his pads

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to de Kock, 1 run
text: good length on his pads, and clipped to the leg side

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to Holder, no run
text: full outside off, from over the stumps. Bit of outswing, taking it away from Holder. Left alone
preText: Maruti Suzuki ASKcricinfo stat: How many times have Ashwin and Chahal dismissed de Kock in the IPL?

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to Holder, no run
text: full outside off. Bit of movement away as he presses forward to defend. Past the outside edge

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to Holder, no run
text: good length, outside off stump. Tries to cut, misses out on the connection

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to Holder, no run
text: ends up as a wide full toss since Holder reaches out to drive and the ball is swinging away. Mistimed to cover point

shortText: Boult to de Kock, no run
text: full from over the wicket. Lands around off stump. Full face of the bat in his front-foot block

full and wide outside off stump. Presses forward and caresses a drive through the covers. Got four written all over it, but Jos Buttler has other plans. Runs towards the boundary, throws in the dive, and slides the ball back in even though he crashes into the boundary line.
full outside off, and he gets into the front-foot drive to the off side
full on middle and leg, and swinging further into leg and perhaps down. Holder can't get the flick, and it hits the front pad. No lbw appeal either
around the stumps. Back of a length and angling into Holder's body. Looks to pull, but mistimed. Bottom-edged onto the deck
inside edge and luck goes Holder's way. Boult went length from around the stumps, and Holder tried to muscle a pull over the leg side. Edged, over the stumps, and races away to fine leg

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to de Kock, 1 leg bye
text: around the stumps. Length ball trying to follow de Kock if he backs away to the leg side. He doesn't, tries to flick, hits the thigh and rolls down to long on

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to Holder, no run
text: over the stumps. Full outside off, enticing Holder to drive. But the ball swings away, and he misses the connection
preText:
Sachin: "You know now, why Mumbai is at bottom of the table."

Jassim : "@sachin they were preparing for 2023 IPL...forgot about this year's ipl"

wkt_text: JO Holder c Ashwin b Prasidh Krishna 8 (17m 14b 2x4 0x6) SR: 57.14
text: in the air and mid on - Ashwin - pockets that with ease. Prasidh bowls short of a length, Holder looks to be in position to pull, but the bat's face is looking up, and has sliced the shot in the air. A fist pump from Prasidh as Super Giants go 14 for 3
crunched over cover for four! Prasidh goes full outside off, Hooda chooses to drive with hard hands. Off the bat's middle, and flies over the infielder

shortText: Prasidh Krishna to Hooda, no run
text: back of a length, fifth-stump line. Hooda rides the bounce, gets on top of it, before cutting to point

full outside off stump. Leans into a drive, well struck, but Buttler flies to his right along the ground from mid off to complete a one-handed stop. Saves three runs, and keeps the pressure up on Super Giants
postText: Kapil Baldawa : "Honestly, what exactly is the rationale of sending 2 finishers at No.3 and 4 respectively? Why not try Hooda at 3? He is in good form and can make use of the PP too and when QDC is still around, he can take care of PP big time. Poor planning from LSG to waste two big hitters"

text: back of a length, on off. Rides the bounce and fends it to the off side. Soft hands
postText: Jamdy: "RR Bowling looks solid.courtesy MALINGAAAA.."

text: full on middle and leg. Swinging into Hooda. Looks to flick it off his toes, but it's a quick ball that zoots through. Hits his front leg, but impact on leg is probably outside leg stump too.
smart shot as Hooda uses Boult's pace and the field placement to ramp this short ball over the infield
full on leg, and flicked well behind square off his boots. Rassie at deep square leg runs towards fine leg and puts in a slide to save two runs

text: full on a stump to stump line. Defended to the off side off the front foot
preText: over the stumps

text: full on middle stump. Defended off the front foot to mid on
preText: Ashwin.

text: around the stumps. Full on middle stump. Pushed to long off for one
preText: Noor: "@Prashant, he wasn't retained because he wasn't that good before his time with Mumbai Indians in 2020. Mumbai deserve some credit for buying him and using him so well."

text: full on off stump. Flicked off his pads to fine leg for a single
full on off stump. Guided off the front foot to the off side
slider. Length ball on off and angling in. Punched to long on

text: almost a yorker on off stump. Ends up as a low full toss and he toe-ends the drive back
preText: First look at Kuldeep Sen. He's tall, touching 6 feet if not crossing it.

good length, on leg stump. Swivels and pulls over deep backward square!

full on middle and leg. Clipped to deep backward square leg

fuller on off, and driven to long-on
